host_about: We are a family staying at the sea during weekends and school vacations, happy to share our house with you!

Hi there, I'm from Amsterdam. I love coffee and music.

I work as online marketing manager but I used to own and operate a coffee bar so I can tell you all about the best local places to eat and drink.

We (me & my girlfriend) live in the southern part of Amsterdam (Schinkelbuurt), it's  a quiet neighborhood in walking distance of shops, bars, restaurant, public transport and a few steps away from Amsterdams Vondelpark. 
We both love to ride our bikes to work, it enhances the already high quality of life in this vivid city.

Hi there! We’re CAP Homes in Amsterdam. Together with our local hosts and over 50 holiday homes distributed across prime locations in the heart of Amsterdam, we are here to make your stay unforgettable. Since 2015, we have been focused on offering holiday accommodations by selecting only the best and coziest apartments in the city for you. We're created several projects as Harbour Suites, Livia's Hideaway and De Vergulden Eenhoorn. We love to focus on personal experience but as well easy/modern way of traveling. Please gloss over our listings carefully to be sure we are good fit for your trip! We appreciate some few words about yourself with your booking, so we get to know each other a bit more before your trip! Thanks!

Hello and  welcome to my home. I am Viola 31 years old.
Originally from the south of Holland but fell in love with the most beautiful city of the Netherlands. 
During the week I work full time but in the weekend I love to discover new bars and restaurants in the city.
I am Eveline and I live in Amsterdam. My favourite activity is travelling and airbnb fits exactly in this picture: meeting new people and their homes in another culture.
Live today like there's no tomorrow...!
Live on a boat, build boats and love boats and like you to host on my boat!
Iamb&b is taking care of my apartment while i'm gone!

I am Zoë and have been living in the centre of amsterdam all my life.
I am the owner of a catering company and cooking school. A hectic but wonderfull life. When home i want to be comfortable in a relaxed athmoshpere.

Hello! 

I am Stijn and I live in Berlin. Actually I am Dutch and I lived for many years in Amsterdam. Because of my job I got the chance to experience this great and lively German city.

Please feel welcome and enjoy your stay in Berlin!

Stijn
Easy going, open minded, respectful of your privacy, happy to connect if you feel like a chat.
i like to meet people. I am intrigued by people.i like to welcome people. I like music art stories

Experienced 5 star airbnb host, who took a few years off from listing.  I now list my own home while I travel.  

Seasoned business and leisure traveler.  Most of my travels center around meeting new people, eat great food, and learning about the culture..
Hallo! Mijn naam is Eva, Ik ben verpleegkundige op de Ambulance. Ik woon in een hele leuke gezellige upcomming wijk in Amsterdam, dichtbij het centrum/jordaan en loopafstand van het Westerpark!
Hi I'm Jochem!

I have a passion for design, art and typography and have a professional background in business development. 

I love good food and great adventures! 
Whether your next trip is for business, or a holiday, I'll be ready to help you!

Friendly hospitable guy ,have been working in the hospitality industry in Canada (Vancouver) and in Amsterdam for a long time.

I have traveled all over north-america,mexico and europe

have a good knowledge of things to see and do in Amsterdam and my aim is to make your stay here as comfortable and interesting as possible
Work at a bank and only rent out my apartment when I am on Holiday! Had to cancel the last 3 listings because I was hit by a car and had a broken arm :)
Easy going Dutch guy! Lived in quite few places around the world, currently settled in Amsterdam. Look forward to meeting you!
We are a young couple from Amsterdam (Netherlands) and love to travel. Our next trip will be to New York to visit our family.

I'm South African and have been living in Europe (London and Amsterdam) for the past 10 years. I also lived in Colombia for almost a year. I speak Afrikaans, English and Spanish. 

I'm an accountant and I currently work as a treasurer at a mining company. 

I love travelling, and I usually jam pack my trips with sightseeing and outdoor activities, rather than staying in one place for too long.
Father of three beautiful childeren, architect, cyclinglover

Ons gezin bestaat uit mijn vriendin en ik, en onze twee 12-jarige zonen. Wij zijn dol op wonen op het water en op Amsterdam. Wij hopen dat onze gasten er ook van zullen genieten!

We are a family of four: two women and two boys age 12. We like to travel and we love living on our houseboat in Amsterdam. We hope our guests will enjoy it as much!
A former professional athlete, currently working as a Journalist. I love to explore new areas, experience cultures and other peoples lifestyles.

My name is Zora, I am 47 years old and I live in Amsterdam with my son  (21) and my daughter (25) I am a social worker and I work with problematic children. I love everything: festivals, camping, dancing, music, sports, reading, my dog and my cat.

Hello possible guest,

My name is Sander Breur, 30 years old and I am a second year PhD student in Physics at the University of Amsterdam. Being born and raised in Amsterdam I just love this city and it's the people. My interests include (beach) volleyball, good food, snowboarding, backpacking, board games and enjoying live in general ;)  

As a guest I will always try to make sure you find the experience you are looking for in Amsterdam. When traveling myself I always enjoy the tips I get from the locals who know where to find the most affordable and best things, so I try to give something back. So ask me anything about the shortest route, the best parties or cheapest places to eat. My own normal schedule is work during the day and sports and social activities at night. 

What I expect from guests is just being respectful towards our nice home :)

If you would like to know anything else, do not hesitate to ask!

Hi im Mahbu, 33 years old, i'm a make up artist, 
with love flor music, food, wine, travel, Amsterdam and much more...

Iamb&b is taking care of my apartment while i'm gone!

Hello I am Nanne, there is nothing special about me. I live my live. I am happy. Iff you come to Amsterdam, I hope you have a fine time. I think you will have a fine time. Iff you have time, it is a wise idea to go out off Amsterdam to the country site. 5 kilometer north off Amsterdam, the countrysite is very good.

I have been living in Amsterdam for 6 years and working as a finance manager for an avivation company. I can't live without music, good food, good wine and great circle of people around me. My favorite movies are Notting Hill, Leon, butterfly effect, the Godfather I, pulp fiction, Good Will Hunting. My favorite books are to kill a mocking bird, the alchemist, Illusions. You will always find my place nice and clean like I like it my self  and I'll do my best to make you feel home.
Hi there, I'm a professional outgoing guy that enjoys art and culture. I enjoy the cultural life of big cities as well as the calm of the countryside and nature.

I'm a professor at the University of Amsterdam. I love to travel and have had a number of wonderful Airbnb stays. Now I'm trying things out as a host. I'm looking forward to finding out how things are from the other side!
Living in amsterdam

Hi!

I'm a free spirit who loves to explore the world. What I like hosting is to meet new people from different cultures all over the world, to have the traveling vibe in daily life. I'm very easy-going and please don't walk on egg shells around me, makes me uncomfortable. During weekdays I'll be off to work, but when I'm home  I'm always in for a chat or a laugh.  

I'm lucky to have my own apartment and that I can share my home with others. I hope to offer guests tranquility and comfort to save up energy so they can fully enjoy the city. 

See you soon!
Rouming
I am a software engineer and have a lovely wife :) who is an architect and two well raised :) children of 14 and 16 years old.

Hello!  I have been living in Amsterdam for over 15 years. I love going to local art shows, theater, the Amsterdam museums and both classical and rock concerts. I also love reading, which you will notice if you come stay with me.
I created a new listing for the same apartment! Looking for some reviews? Look at the ones for my other listing!

Hi! My name is Linda Oostveen and I am a Creative Marketeer from The Netherlands. I travel much en really enjoy having a chill and active time at the same time, when I am on hollidays. I am adventirous person and love to go out and see new things on my own!

Hi! I am Simone and live in one of the nicest areas of Amsterdam, in my opinion ;-) I live here with great pleasure and what the city has to offer. I love to travel and also using Airbnb during my holidays. I think this is a nice way to middle in real life from that spot. This is the reason why I want to give other travelers that way of experience Amsterdam.

Ciao I am Carlo.....Italian artist and Engineer moved to Amsterdam 3 years ago....
In the apartment you are viewing I developed my Atelier in which I do weekly workshops and Art events. 
So enjoy the experience of spending time in a real art atelier surrounded by paintings.
Amsterdam based

After traveling (worrking as guide expedtion leader in South America and Antarctica and sailing(tallships) around the world. I thought my roots would settle better in water last year I moved to this great houseboat. a quite street with sounds of the zoo and lots of green make it a little oasis. in the hectic city of Amsterdam where is allways something fun to do and see 

Looking forward to meet you!! 
Tjalling Halbertsma

Outgoing en ingoing. I love to make people feel at ease and create the atmosphere where they feel at home. That's why I have created this place: homely and cosy, yet modern, spacious and very light. Just like me....:-)

Hi! I am Rosa, I love my city Amsterdam, because there is always something to do. I have a passion for sports and nutrition. Furthermore I love to go dancing, trying out new hotspots and drinking wine with friends. If you want to, I will share my favorite places and things to do in Amsterdam!

My apartment is just like me: welcoming & sharing inspiration. It is a mix & match of the places I have visited and the people i've met. I traveled a lot and I've been to South Africa, Colombia, Peru, Costa Rica, Thailand, Indonesia, North America and through Europe. But I still love coming home in this apartment and just relax!

Hello, I'm Erik, in my early thirties and love to explore the world!

I've lived in Mexico and Spain and have been lots of other countries in Central-America, Asia, the Middle-East and many European cities, my wish list is only expanding. Although I love to travel and get to know many different cultures, I still have a passion for my hometown Amsterdam that I would really love to share with you! Not only during my travels but also when I'm in Amsterdam I'm always searching for local hotspots such as cozy lunchrooms, food markets, restaurants, museums, exhibitions and musically orientated places and events such as concerts and festivals. Because I lived in Amsterdam for many years I can recommend you all kinds of places that will make your trip unforgettable!
Hi! We are Daniel and Merel. We live in Amsterdam, it's our favorite city. We love traveling, craft beers and meeting cool, inspiring people.
Iamb&b is taking care of my apartment while I am gone!

I’m James, and live together with my fiancé, Georgia here in Amsterdam. We are Australian expats who’s careers brought us to his wonderful city, and the rest is history! We’ve been here for 3 years now, and we call it home. 

We love traveling (sometimes permanently), socializing with friends and great food and wine. 

Looking forward to welcoming you to our home and helping you fall in love with this charming town just like we did! 

James & Georgia.
I'm a mother of 2 from London but living in Amsterdam and married to a Californian. We love to cook, eat out and watch movies.
Open, fun, honest, social person. Always open for an adventure. Regarding to renting rooms/ apartments i am neat and responsible. Text me to find more out more about me.

Hi There!

We've travelled all around the world and noticed that there's a humongous shortage on accommodations with a personal touch and homey atmosphere.

We offer high-end luxury apartments at the historic Keizersgracht Canal in Amsterdam and our aim is make your stay to your absolute satisfaction.
You will feel Home away from Home for sure.
See ya soon! Peter & Jasmin
Amsterdam, The Netherlands
I am a spiritual guy who loves diving, having great conversations about life and sometimes just plain fun

I'm working as an editor at large/freelance journalist. I'm a friendly and polite person (so I like to think), who likes to eat in small restaurants, drink with friends, and likes to see films and docu's. At home I love to eat chocolate, chips and chicken.  I'm interested in different kind of musicstyles: from hiphop to classic. Fan of Messi, caparinha's and Will and Grace.

I'm a 39 year old professional trainer, traveling quite a bit in a lot of different cultures. I love making people feel comfortable and am always curious about other people's experiences, big or small. 

I love watching movies, cooking, running and delivering inspiring training sessions. I also love taking pictures and traveling. my favorite places to go to are South Africa, Thailand, Vietnam and Eastern Europe. All these places are great for winding down after a couple of months of hard work, and all have great culture, cooks and beautiful scenery.

Ik woon met Joost en onze twee zonen in een heerlijke buurt van Amsterdam. We genieten van de stad en alle leuke restaurants, cultuur en Vondelpark op loopafstand. Onze vrije tijd brengen we graag tijd door met de kinderen, familie en vrienden. We sporten veel (hockey, hardlopen, yoga, fietsen, golf) en houden van lekker eten. En  hoe kan je beter je weekend beginnen dan met het gezin op vrijdagavond, met chips en frisdrank/wijn op de bank, een goeie film met elkaar te kijken!
I'm a designer/researcher. I love cooking, traveling, the outdoors, and reading.
We are two young profesionals and avid travelers. We enjoy hosting and meeting new people. We love Amsterdam and our neighborhood, and enjoy helping others to fall in love with it.
Iamb&b is taking care of my apartment while I am gone!

Hi,

My name is Nitin. I am currently travelling constantly for my job so for this reason i joined airbnb.

My apartment located in the southern part of Amsterdam near the RAI is a luxe 1 bedroom apartment with 4 sleep possibilities and I would love to welcome you as my guest.

Hey I am Krista, I love living in Amsterdam. And super happy with my house. Hope you like it too. I travel as often as possible, so most off the time I am not there to do the check-in myself. But you will be fine. :-)

I love to travel and meet new people. I travel regularly for my business so I also get to experience local business cultures which I find to be inspiring. To relax, I like to read about various topics. With relaxing music and a good drink  :) Furthermore I just enjoy all typical good things of life + flamenco music + ancient history + space travel ;)
